field.description:
Input/Output physical signals/terminals naming rules.
                For each value of the Parameter entity a physical signals could be generated, according to the following naming convention:
                    deviceName + parameterName or parameterName + physicalAddress (e.g.: Channel + PhysicalAddress for Modbus)
                The physicalAdddress suffix will have the following syntax:
                    %<memory area prefix> ( <size prefix> )? <memory position>
                where
                    memory area prefix : I | Q | M
                    size prefix : X | B | W | D
                    memory position : number ( .number ) ( Depends on the target system )

                An alternative is to use the following semantic signal naming rules:

                AHU fan physical input signals
                    ahuFanDriveControlWord : WORD;
                    ahuFanDriveStatusWord : WORD;
                    ahuFanDriveRO1 : BOOL; ( Relay output 1 )

                Air renewal fan physical input signals
                    airRenewalFanDriveControlWord : WORD;
                    airRenewalFanDriveStatusWord : WORD;
                    airRenewalFanDriveRO1 : BOOL; ( Relay output 1 )

                Cold glycol circulating pump physical input signals
                    coldGlycolPumpMotorStarterSignalingContact : BOOL;
                    coldGlycolPumpMotorStarterShuntTrip : BOOL;
                    coldGlycolPumpContactorSignalingContact : BOOL;

                 ...
